[[File:Telekinetic Grab icon (mobile).png|left]]
'''Telekinetic Grab''' requires a [[Magic]] level of 33 as well as an [[air rune]] and a [[law rune]] to cast. Doing so grants 43 Magic [[experience]]. It is recommended that players use a [[staff of air]] when casting this spell, as the spell will then only require a law rune to cast.

It is used to pick up an item (or pile of stackable items) from a distance, including over or through obstacles such as fences, gates, and rivers. It is useful when picking up item spawns that are guarded by dangerous monsters, such as the [[wine of Zamorak]] in the [[Chaos Temple (Asgarnia)|Chaos Temple]]. It is also sometimes required in quests in order to pick up items needed in the quest but that are guarded by [[Non-player character|NPCs]] or otherwise unreachable.

There are only a few items, such as [[Ahab's beer]], [[dragon token]] and equipable reward items from [[Achievement_Diary|achievement diaries]] which cannot be picked up with Telekinetic Grab.

